def ocr_node.OCR.convert_to_cv_image (   self,
  data 
)

when image callback function get the ros image message, convert it to cv_image(for opencv format)

Parameters
[in]dataros image message
Note
input constraints:
- none
output constraints:
- cv_image should not be empty
- cv_image should be sized 640 x 480
- cv_image should be color image (3 channel)
Returns
cv_image converted to opencv format image

◆ get_binary()

def ocr_node.OCR.get_binary (   self,
  img 
)

before getting contour from image, we should convert gray image to binary image

it is important to use apropriate image format(h or s or v), and set apropriate threshold value.

Parameters
[in]imgh or s or v image
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be gray image (1 channel)
output constraints:
- binary_image should not be empty
- binary_image should be binary image (1 channel)
Returns
bin_img: output binary image

◆ get_hsv()

def ocr_node.OCR.get_hsv (   self,
  img 
)

for detecting marker, we pre-process image to hsv.

the function return h, s, v image. for detecting marker, we're gonna use h image cause color of marker is yellow and it's opposite of micropipette body color(body color is indigo)

Parameters
[in]imgdraft_roi_img should be input
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be color image (3 channel)
output constraints:
- h_image should not be empty
- h_image should be mono image (1 channel)
- s_image should not be empty
- s_image should be mono image (1 channel)
- v_image should not be empty
- v_image should be mono image (1 channel)
Returns
h_img, s_img, v_img: all images sould be return

def ocr_node.OCR.remove_noise (   self,
  img 
)

remove unnessary contour, so we prevent error and focus on important data

this method reffered from "https://pyimagesearch.com/2015/02/09/removing-contours-image-using-python-opencv/"

Parameters
[in]imgbinary image
Note
input constraints:
- image should not be empty
- image should be binary image (1 channel)
output constraints:
- noise_removed_binary_image should not be empty
- noise_removed_binary_image should be binary image (1 channel)
Returns
noise_removed_bin_img: output binary image which the noise is removed
